    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1901</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Russell reports that the Venezuelan Government claims that the State
                    Department, Navy Department, and United States legation at Caracas are aware of
                    the law upon the subject of closed ports of Venezuela, and menacingly repeats
                    request for explanation of the <hi rend="italic">Mayflower’s</hi> entrance of a
                    closed port in the island of Margarita.</p>
                <p>A reply is requested.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
